'''義大利即興喜劇'''（{{lang-it|Commedia dell'arte}}）是16世紀在[[義大利|義大利]]出現的一種[[戲劇|戲劇]]，其特點是戴著[[面具|面具]]的角色，是由女演員{{le|Isabella Andreini|Isabella Andreini}}發明<ref name=":02">{{Cite book|title=The Italian Comedy: The Improvisation Scenarios Lives Attributes Portraits and Masks of the Illustrious Characters of the Commedia dell'Arte|url=https://archive.org/details/italiancomedyimp0000duch|last=Ducharte|first=Pierre Louis|publisher=Dover Publication, INC.|year=1966|isbn=0486216799|location=New York|pages=[https://archive.org/details/italiancomedyimp0000duch/page/17 17]|quote=|via=}}</ref>，是以[[喜剧小品|喜剧小品]]<!--或{{le|戲劇腳本|Scenario}}-->為基礎的[[即興劇場|即興劇場]]<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|title=The Routledge Companion to Commedia Dell'Arte|author1=Chaffee, Judith  |author2=Crick, Olly|publisher=Rutledge Taylor and Francis Group|year=2015|isbn=978-0-415-74506-2|location=London and New York|pages=1,|quote=|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.factionoffools.org/history|title=Faction Of Fools|date=|website=|publisher=|access-date=|archive-date=2017-03-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170313021054/http://www.factionoffools.org/history|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。義大利即興喜劇中的一個特色是{{le|插科打诨|lazzi}}<ref>{{Cite book|title=Lazzi:  jhe Comic Routine of the Commeida dell'Arte|url=https://archive.org/details/lazzicomicroutin00gord|last=Gordon|first=Mel|publisher=Preforming Arts Journal Publications|year=1983|isbn=0-933826-69-9|location=New York|pages=[https://archive.org/details/lazzicomicroutin00gord/page/4 4]|quote=|via=}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite book|title=Playing Commedia A Training Guide to Commedia Techniques|last=Grantham|first=Barry|publisher=Heinemann Drama|year=2000|isbn=0-325-00346-7|location=United Kingdom|pages=3, 6, 7}}</ref>，另一個特色是其中{{le|滑稽演員|Harlequin}}會以[[哑剧|哑剧]]的方式呈現<ref>{{Cite book|title=A History Of Pantomime|last=Broadbent|first=R.J.|publisher=Benjamin Blom, Inc.|year=1901|location=New York|pages=62}}</ref>。

義大利即興喜劇中有許多的[[定型角色|定型角色]]，例如愚笨的老人、狡猾的僕人、看似充滿勇氣的軍官等。主要角色有僕人、老人、愛人及船長等<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":3">{{Cite web|url=http://www.factionoffools.org/history|title=Faction of Fools {{!}} A History of Commedia dell'Arte|website=www.factionoffools.org|access-date=2016-12-09|archive-date=2016-12-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161211111229/http://www.factionoffools.org/history|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

